An Act relative to oversight of the sex offender registry board.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Subsection (a) of section 178E of chapter 6 of the General Laws, as
2 appearing in the 2022 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting after the words “data to
3 the”, in line 17, the following words:- “state police and”.
4 SECTION 2. Section 178H of said chapter 6, as so appearing, is hereby amended by
5 inserting the following subsection:-
6 “(c) Whenever the board determines that an offender knowingly and intentionally: (i)
7 fails to register; (ii) fails to verify registration information; (iii) fails to provide notice of a
8 change of address; or (iv) knowingly provides false information; the board shall transmit relevant
9 data to the state police who shall seek an arrest warrant for the offender.”
